parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the heater core can cause antifreeze to leak into the passenger compartment, leading to visibility issues, burns, and difficulty navigating the vehicle.
symptoms: Steam or antifreeze coats the windshield
antifreeze leaks into the passenger compartment
minor burns to the driver's lower leg area
steam fills the passenger compartment making it difficult to navigate.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Fuel Leakage and Noisy Fan Motor Shaft
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Fuel leakage can cause a fire, and a noisy fan motor shaft can lead to engine compartment fires.
symptoms: Fuel leakage in the engine compartment

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Timing belt failure can cause the vehicle to stall, leading to safety hazards, and can also destroy engine valves.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Transmission and Engine Cooling System Malfunctions
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission and engine cooling system malfunctions can cause the vehicle to overheat, hesitate, and stall, leading to safety hazards.
Power window malfunction can cause the windows to operate by themselves, leading to safety hazards and inconvenience.
symptoms: need to pull fuse to stop
but then they are not operable at all.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the heater core can cause the sudden release of hot coolant and steam into the passenger compartment, reducing visibility, and potentially causing burns or injuries to the driver and passengers.
symptoms: Steam or fog coming through the air vents
hot coolant leaking into the passenger compartment
difficulty seeing out of the windshield
and a sudden loss of visibility.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition system can cause the engine to stall while in motion, leading to a loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: repeated attempts are required to start the vehicle
the vehicle starts after adjusting the steering wheel and "thumping" it up and down.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause fires, stalling, and malfunctioning of various vehicle components, leading to a loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Flames coming from under the fog lights
wires from the battery to the dash catching on fire

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake system can cause the vehicle to lose stopping power, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The brake pedal goes to the floor

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the ABS system can cause the vehicle to lose traction, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The ABS warning lights come on
the vehicle won't stop on snow or ice
the brake pedal goes to the floor
the ABS system never worked properly.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Premature Tire Wear due to Disc Brakes
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The premature wear on tires can cause loss of traction, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The disc brakes cause premature wear on tires.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the ignition system can cause the vehicle to continue running after the ignition is turned off, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle continues to run after the ignition is turned off and key is removed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the air conditioner can cause discomfort and distraction while driving.
The malfunction of the sunroof can cause inconvenience and expense.
symptoms: A small part breaks on the sunroof track
requiring replacement of the entire sunroof mechanism.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fog lights can cause reduced visibility while driving.
symptoms: The fog light lenses fog up or fill up with water and then crack from heat.
